 or tree density. In general, sites with bigger shape indices had fewer captures. Ten of the 20 most captured species showed no significant difference between the three habitats. The bat communities in Alter do Cha\u02dc o were not strongly affected by forest fragmentation, and the savannas did not appear to act as an ecological barrier to bats.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Bernard, Enrico", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fenton, M. Brock", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/89ba6659c8dcd38e9f800cfe0c6a85d8", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/6c5303560e7212c615031ae38408318b55523d6418f56697f2a43d3be86f2207", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/6I7JWHXJ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/6I7JWHXJ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/379a7fcf429797a32618d7311b246851!/b96150-98645", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/0157e8ec3f1f8eb877e7b6cd6fde26bc", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "3", "pages": "332-343", "title": "Biological Conservation", "volume": "134"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/89ba6659c8dcd38e9f800cfe0c6a85d8"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:6I7JWHXJ"}, {"identifier": "10.1016/j.biocon.2006.07.021"}], "communities": [{"id": 